snippet.textDisplay: There has to be the grey area when it comes to information on the internet. One, you're basically saying that (to put some label on) "Information Source 1" is the truth, no matter how it's concluded. Now here's the thing. "Information Source 1" may very well start as the truth. But that doesn't mean it will stay the truth if it's manipulated later. Which kind of ties into my second point. Anything worth knowing is worth atleast some degree of independent research. And hopefully from multiple perspectives. For one, it ensures better accuracy, for as the old saying goes: There's two sides to every story and the truth usually lies somewhere in between. So the grey is where you do independent research. It has to be there. It keeps any "Information Source" honest. Lastly, it's an even worse idea because it stifles critical thinking. We're probably already deficient in cognitive stamina as a society just as a result of everything already being automated. Now you're saying with this move, we could just not think about it and go with one source. Well, that's what stupid people do now. We'd have pudding for brains in 2 generations. A society of unthinking zombies. No thanks.

snippet.textDisplay:
Trying to finish everything you've done but it is kinda random. For instance, when Riley was doing his solo sail, you had a bunch of Vlogs that said for instance, "E4 Daily Vlog 9 of 21" that insinuates there are more but where? I found 2 and got tired of looking for more. It would be nice if all were in sequential order 1 through ∞ and if you do make a group of off subject videos, insert them as a group sequentially also. I'm so confused...
It took me a bit more than 2 months to watch every video I've found, and gave them ALL a proper 👍. Can't believe all the viewers who don't. Keep up the good work. Oh my gosh, what are you feeding Lenny? he's growing like a bamboo shoot.
Oh, I also noticed quite a time delay between the release of a video and the date it was shot. It made a huge disconnect between us. Like I could actually feel like I was with you guys then felt about maybe a week out, and now months out. Kinda spoils it because I like to track you on Google earth, every place you've mentions you've stayed at I put a little sail boat Icon, the date and the episode #. Was kinda fun until you live casted your last trip from New York and it came out what, 4, 5 months later. The thrill is gone.....

snippet.textDisplay: I live just 45 minutes outside of NYC and when I get a chance I love going in there. A few of my favorite places are Greenwich Village, Chinatown, Little Italy, the Lower Eastside. Specifically you might really like to have a drink at McSorley's Ale House which is the oldest ale house in the city and loaded with fascinating history. Also , checkout the Tenement Museum on Orchard St. in the Lower Eastside. You already found Central Park which I love. While there you might take a walk through the Waldorf Astoria . Also take a walk by the Dakota which is where John Lennon lived and unfortunately died. Rockefeller Center with the Xmas tree. Wollman skating rink in the park.
